App::papersway
--------------

This is an implementation of PaperWM-like scrollable tiling window management
for Sway/i3wm.  If you like Sway/i3wm's commitments to stability, avoiding
scope creep etc. but dislike the window management model, papersway might be
of interest.

papersway -- PaperWM-like window management using i3-ipc.

papersway-msg -- Script for sending user commands to papersway.

See also:

    https://i3wm.org/
    https://swaywm.org/
    https://github.com/paperwm/PaperWM

    https://material-shell.com/
    https://spatial-shell.app/

INSTALLATION

To install these programs, run the following commands:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make
    % make install

If you don't see Makefile.PL, it can be generated from dist.ini using
Dist::Zilla's 'dzil' program.

On Debian 13 or later & Ubuntu 24.10 or later, 'apt-get install papersway'.

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for these programs with
the man command.

    % man papersway

You can also look for information at:

    Project homepage
        https://spwhitton.name/tech/code/papersway/

    RT, CPAN's bug tracker (please see CONTRIBUTING)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=App-papersway

    MetaCPAN
        https://metacpan.org/release/papersway

